Ntop.geometry:	+0+0
Ntop*background:	grey75
Ntop*foreground:	black
!
! There are two ways to modify the background color for applications:
!
!1. Use a X color name to specify the background color.  Specify the following:
!	Ntop*appbgName:		xcolor name
!   For example:
!	Ntop*appbgName:		grey50
!
!2. Specify an integer 0-255 to specify the RGB component.  For example:
!	Ntop*appbgRed:		200
!	Ntop*appbgGreen:	20
!	Ntop*appbyBlue:		200
!
! If an invalid X Color name is specified, the color components will be
! used if they are valid. Otherwise black will be used. If a color component
! that component will be set to 0.
!
! WARNING: If a valid appbgName is also specified, the color components 
!          will have no effect
